video.title: Stargate SG-1
video.synopsis: Stargate Command roars into action when Jack O'Neill and his crew find a Stargates map that lets them combat alien maneuvers all across the galaxy.

episodes.synopsis: Col. Jack O'Neill and his SG-1 team -- Daniel Jackson, Teal'c and Capt. Samantha Carter -- set out to explore the mysteries of the Stargate.
episodes.title: Children of the Gods

episodes.synopsis: Doctors discover a Goa'uld larvae has attached itself to Kawalsky's brain and the soldier must undergo a risky operation.
episodes.title: The Enemy Within

episodes.synopsis: Capt. Samantha Carter fights for true love on a planet where for equality the women are treated as property.
episodes.title: Emancipation

episodes.synopsis: After returning from a new planet of primitives, O'Neill and the SG-1 team begin a startling transformation.
episodes.title: The Broca Divide

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill and the SG-1 team are sent to investigate the disappearance of SG-9, only to discover that Capt. Jonas Hanson is ruling the planet like a god.
episodes.title: The First Commandment

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill is knocked out and replaced by an alien double while on a mission.
episodes.title: Cold Lazarus

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team learns a lesson in harmony from an alien race.
episodes.title: The Nox

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill begins to age at an alarming rate of 10 years a day and the SG-1 team can't stop it.
episodes.title: Brief Candle

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill and Teal'c are trapped in an underground labyrinth and must fight for their lives against Unas, the original Goa'uld host.
episodes.title: Thor's Hammer

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team finds itself without a way home when they attempt to rescue the one person who traveled through the Stargate more than 50 years earlier.
episodes.title: The Torment of Tantalus

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c returns to Chulak in an attempt to stop his son Rya'c from becoming a slave to the Goa'ulds.
episodes.title: Bloodlines

episodes.synopsis: Daniel Jackson is presumed dead after an alien abducts him and sends the rest of the SG-1 team home.
episodes.title: Fire and Water

episodes.synopsis: A Goa'uld who has taken on the persona of the Egyptian sex goddess, Hathor, casts her deadly spell over all the men on the Stargate base.
episodes.title: Hathor

episodes.synopsis: The team rescues a little girl who survived a deadly disease, only to find she's a human time bomb designed by the Goa'uld to destroy the Stargate.
episodes.title: Singularity

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c is put on trial by the son of a man he jailed when he served the evil Goa'uld Apophis.
episodes.title: Cor-ai

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team rescues a group of advanced aliens but must risk court-martial to prevent the aliens' technology from falling into the wrong hands.
episodes.title: Enigma

episodes.synopsis: A Stargate malfunction leaves O'Neill and Carter stranded in an icy crevasse on an unknown planet.
episodes.title: Solitudes

episodes.synopsis: A strange man implants the consciousness of the SG-1 team in robots.
episodes.title: Tin Man

episodes.synopsis: Daniel Jackson is pulled into an alternate reality where he sees Earth being invaded by the Goa'uld.
episodes.title: There But for the Grace of God

episodes.synopsis: A powerful U.S. Senator vows to shut down the Stargate project despite Daniel Jackson's warnings of an eminent Goa'uld invasion.
episodes.title: Politics

episodes.synopsis: As the government prepares to mothball the Stargate project, O'Neill and the SG-1 team take an unauthorized trip to try to stop the Goa'uld invasion.
episodes.title: Within the Serpent's Grasp

episodes.synopsis: As a fleet of Goa'uld warships heads toward Earth, the Stargate facility sends the best of American society through the Stargate to a safe Alpha site.
episodes.title: The Serpent's Lair

episodes.synopsis: As the SG-1 team hopes to rescue the survivors of a planet attacked by the Goa'uld, Carter's body is taken over by a Goa'uld, which returns to Earth.
episodes.title: In the Line of Duty

episodes.synopsis: While exploring a planet, the team is approached by a man who asks for help escaping from a pursuer, but they discover the man is a fleeing murderer.
episodes.title: Prisoners

episodes.synopsis: The team discovers a dome full of chambers, each containing an unconscious person. As the team investigates, they're trapped and knocked unconscious.
episodes.title: The Gamekeeper

episodes.synopsis: When the team encounters Jaffa warriors delivering the precious element Naquadah, they are captured and forced to slave in the Naquadah mines.
episodes.title: Need

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team returns to the planet Cimmeria after learning the Goa'uld have invaded, and they make some striking discoveries on the planet.
episodes.title: Thor's Chariot

episodes.synopsis: The team finds an orb that sends out electromagnetic signals. They are intrigued by its power source, which seems to have lasted for millennia.
episodes.title: Message in a Bottle

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c's mentor arrives through the Stargate with shocking news: The Goa'uld Apophis survived the destruction of his ship and kidnapped Teal'c's son.
episodes.title: Family

episodes.synopsis: Jackson and Teal'c travel back to Abydos. Daniel learns that his wife is nine months pregnant and the father plans to use the baby as his new host.
episodes.title: Secrets

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill and the SG-1 team are attacked by giant insects. Teal'c is stung, and when he returns to Earth, a strange transformation begins.
episodes.title: Bane

episodes.synopsis: Carter dreams that she sees the Tok'ra or rebel Goa'uld through the eyes of Jolinar and must go on a mission with the SG-1 team to find the Tok'ra.
episodes.title: The Tok'ra: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The Tok'ra turn down SG-1's request for an alliance against the Goa'uld because no earthling will be a host for Selmak, a Tok'ra whose host is dying.
episodes.title: The Tok'ra: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: After the team discovers the element Trinium on the planet PXY-887, its inhabitants fire a Trinium arrow through the Stargate, wounding O'Neill.
episodes.title: Spirits

episodes.synopsis: When an imposter SG-1 team steals the climate-controlling Touchstone from the planet Madrona, the weather deteriorates, threatening the inhabitants.
episodes.title: Touchstone

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill receives the knowledge of the inventors of the Stargate. But the knowledge is too complex for humans and will cause O'Neill to lose his mind.
episodes.title: The Fifth Race

episodes.synopsis: While attempting to save SG-10 from a black hole, the SG-1 team activates the Stargate and exposes themselves to the hole's gravitational pull.
episodes.title: A Matter of Time

episodes.synopsis: When the SG-1 team stumbles upon the chamber of former Goa'uld enemy Ma'chello, they fall victim to his powerful body-swapping invention.
episodes.title: Holiday

episodes.synopsis: Apophis throws himself at the mercy of the team, who grant him sanctuary. Apophis promises all the knowledge of the Goa'uld in return for a new body.
episodes.title: Serpent's Song

episodes.synopsis: Sent to recover a crashed UAV plane on another world, the team discovers those living on the planet are friendly, gentle and far simpler than humans.
episodes.title: One False Step

episodes.synopsis: A young boy announces to the SG-1 team that the Goa'uld destroyed his planet, Reetalia, and now Reetou rebels intend to kill all human beings.
episodes.title: Show and Tell

episodes.synopsis: The team is propelled to a facility in 1969. Carrying a letter Gen. Hammond gave her, a young Hammond tells Carter the letter is from his future self.
O'Neill is told that he's been frozen for 79 years and the rest of the SG-1 team perished long ago. But is it real, or is it a Goa'uld simulation?
episodes.title: Out of Mind

episodes.synopsis: On Hathor's planet, Carter and Jackson can only watch as Hathor implants O'Neill with a Goa'uld symbiote. Hammond sends six SG units to rescue SG-1.
episodes.title: Into the Fire

episodes.synopsis: Carter's father hunts for the Goa'uld system lord Seth. A computer search reveals that Seth has maintained power on Earth for thousands of years.
episodes.title: Seth

episodes.synopsis: Thor tells O'Neill that the Goa'uld lords plan to attack Earth. He offers his help in negotiating a peace treaty. Three lords attend the summit.
episodes.title: Fair Game

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team discovers a room containing Goa'uld corpses. After Jackson touches a tablet, he begins to hear voices and see nightmarish visions.
episodes.title: Legacy

episodes.synopsis: In the pursuit of knowledge, Col. Jack O'Neill, Teal'c and Dr. Daniel Jackson travel to the planet Orban as part of an exchange program.
episodes.title: Learning Curve

episodes.synopsis: An alternate-reality version of Carter and the deceased Kawalsky are found in Area 51. To transport themselves to Earth, they used the Quantum Mirror.
episodes.title: Point of View

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 is snared in an invisible force field by bounty hunter Aris Boch. Aris takes them to his ship, which is completely invisible from the outside.
episodes.title: Deadman Switch

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 arrives at a village and frees Mary, a woman who's been tied to a stake. They learn that she's a sacrifice for a demon that plagues the village.
episodes.title: Demons

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 finds a group of SG soldiers battling a Jaffa army. Believing the soldiers to be the SG-11 team, O'Neill and the others provide assistance.
episodes.title: Rules of Engagement

episodes.synopsis: During a rescue of captured Abydonians, Jackson sees his wife, Sha're, watching the activity from a tent. Sha're is actually the Goa'uld Amaunet.
episodes.title: Forever in a Day

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 travels to a planet whose inhabitants all have amnesia. They have no memory of their lives and report that their elders and children are missing.
episodes.title: Past and Present

episodes.synopsis: Carter's father, Jacob, and his Tok'ra symbiote have been captured by the evil Goa'uld system lord Sokar and are imprisoned on a moon called Netu.
episodes.title: Jolinar's Memories

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 and Martouf have been captured on Netu by one of its denizens, who wants to use their information to overthrow the Goa'uld system lord Sokar.
episodes.title: The Devil You Know

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 learns that part of Stargate Command has been sealed off because of a chemical leak. Dr. Fraiser injects each member of the team with a sedative.
episodes.title: Foothold

episodes.synopsis: The Tollan Narim invites SG-1 to participate in a ritual known as Triad. Only when SG-1 shows up do they learn that Triad is a ceremony of justice.
episodes.title: Pretense

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 steps through the Stargate on its way to a paradise planet and ends up at Stargate Command. Hammond tells the team they were gone for 15 hours.
episodes.title: Urgo

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill and the rest of SG-1 have established ties with a village on the planet Edora and its leader, with whom O'Neill shares a mutual attraction.
episodes.title: A Hundred Days

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill becomes annoyed when the Tollans think that any weaponry given to Earth would more likely be used on them than against the Goa'uld.
episodes.title: Shades of Grey

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team travels to the planet Bedrosia, where the planet's two cultures have been at war over their beliefs regarding the Stargate.
episodes.title: New Ground

episodes.synopsis: Bra'tac arrives at Stargate Command pleading for medical assistance. He announces that his home planet has been brutally attacked by Apophis.
episodes.title: Maternal Instinct

episodes.synopsis: Jackson becomes intrigued when the video transmission from a mobile probe reveals a huge Mayan pyramid with a glowing crystal skull in its center.
episodes.title: Crystal Skull

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill is engulfed in a white glow and disappears. Maj. Samantha Carter immediately recognizes that O'Neill has been transported away by the Asgard.
episodes.title: Nemesis

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 returns to Stargate Command with news that Earth has been saved from the Replicators, but they soon learn that one of the creatures still lives.
episodes.title: Small Victories

episodes.synopsis: Gen. Hammond sends SG-1 on a humanitarian mission to deliver food and medical supplies to the planet Euronda, which is under attack.
episodes.title: The Other Side

episodes.synopsis: Anise asks Stargate Command for help in testing mysterious armband devices. Anise believes they could be a weapon in their war against the Goa'uld.
episodes.title: Upgrades

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 responds to an incoming wormhole with their ally Bra'tac's signal and greets Shan'auc, who tells them that she's come on behalf of Bra'tac.
episodes.title: Crossroads

episodes.synopsis: During a meeting with the Tok'ra high council, Maj. Graham goes berserk, firing uncontrollably upon the Tok'ra before taking his own life.
episodes.title: Divide and Conquer

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team meets Malikai, a human explorer from another world who shares Jackson's interest in an alien computer covered in a Latin-like script.
episodes.title: Window of Opportunity

episodes.synopsis: When the Stargate won't open, the team learns that the Russians have their own Stargate, apparently recovered after an Asgard ship crashed on Earth.
episodes.title: Watergate

episodes.synopsis: While conducting an archaeological dig, Jackson discovers a primordial Goa'uld symbiote, an ancient predatory version of SG-1's parasitical enemies.
episodes.title: The First Ones

episodes.synopsis: Thanks to SG-1, a civilization known as the Enkarans has been transplanted from a Goa'uld slave planet to a safer, more hospitable world.
episodes.title: Scorched Earth

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 awakens in a mysterious underground complex, with no memory of their previous lives. In fact, they seem to possess a whole new set of memories.
episodes.title: Beneath the Surface

episodes.synopsis: An individual claims to possess knowledge of government conspiracies, from the Kennedy cover-up to microwave harassment of Libertarian candidates.
episodes.title: Point of No Return

episodes.synopsis: A test of an experimental spacecraft adapted from two Goa'uld Death Gliders goes awry, sending O'Neill and Teal'c hurtling out of Earth's orbit.
episodes.title: Tangent

episodes.synopsis: When Jackson's old archaeology professor, Dr. Jordan, dies in a lab explosion, Daniel pays a return visit to his old academic stomping grounds.
episodes.title: The Curse

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c is captured by the Goa'uld. The rest of SG-1, unaware of his fate, are dispatched to thwart a burgeoning alliance between Apophis and Heru'ur.
episodes.title: The Serpent's Venom

episodes.synopsis: When Hammond announces he's stepping down as head of Stargate Command, O'Neill suspects there's more to Hammond's decision than he's letting on.
episodes.title: Chain Reaction

episodes.synopsis: It's 2010, and a lot has happened in 10 years. The Goa'uld have been defeated, and diseases such as cancer have been wiped out.
SG-1 is called to Abydos to investigate a strange phenomenon: a whirling sandstorm that seems to whisper Dr. Daniel Jackson's name.
episodes.title: Absolute Power

episodes.synopsis: One member of an SG unit has committed suicide, and others, including Jackson, are near death. The answer could lie in a strange off-world temple.
episodes.title: The Light

episodes.synopsis: During a visit to the Air Force Academy, Carter makes the acquaintance of Jennifer Hailey, a promising young cadet with a rebellious streak.
episodes.title: Prodigy

episodes.synopsis: Stargate Command is infected by a probe that uploads its program into the computers, where it accesses data on the Stargate program and its personnel.
episodes.title: Entity

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 returns to Juna, formerly known as P3X-729, a planet they -- or, rather, robot duplicates of them -- helped free from Goa'uld enslavement.
episodes.title: Double Jeopardy

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 visits the Tok'ra home world. They arrive at Vorash on Cronos's ship -- one of the spoils they claimed following their recent battle with him.
episodes.title: Exodus

episodes.synopsis: After losing Teal'c to Apophis, O'Neill, Carter, Daniel and Jacob find themselves aboard Cronus's ship, stranded in a remote part of the galaxy.
episodes.title: Enemies

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c's body has been saved from Apophis's ship, but his mind is still loyal to Goa'uld. Bra'tac arrives at SGC to assist in "deprogramming" Teal'c.
episodes.title: Threshold

episodes.synopsis: While investigating ancient ruins on a distant planet, SG-1 finds a huge alien device that Carter believes could be a weapon of incredible power.
episodes.title: Ascension

episodes.synopsis: After coming under fire on an alien world, Carter, Daniel and Teal'c return and report that O'Neill stayed behind to protect a wounded Lt. Tyler.
episodes.title: The Fifth Man

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 emerges on a world known as K'Tau, a protected planet of Asgard where the people still worship the Norse gods.
episodes.title: Red Sky

episodes.synopsis: During Cassandra's 16th birthday celebration, a kiss causes electricity to surge from her body.
episodes.title: Rite of Passage

episodes.synopsis: After befriending the Unas known as Chaka, Daniel places surveillance cameras on the Unas' planet so that he can study their alien ways.
episodes.title: Beast of Burden

episodes.synopsis: When SG-1 explores the entrance of an ancient step pyramid on a remote world, they are surprised to discover a package of Russian cigarettes.
episodes.title: The Tomb

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 travels to the planet Tollana to attend the funeral of their old acquaintance, Chancellor Omoc.
episodes.title: Between Two Fires

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 returns from an off-world mission proudly announcing that they've met a highly advanced alien race willing to form an alliance with Earth.
A Russian transport vehicle is ambushed, and Jaffa is taken by force. Meanwhile, mysterious men dressed in black abduct Carter.
episodes.title: Desperate Measures

episodes.synopsis: An alien ship is spotted heading toward Earth. SG-1 determines that it's related to Marty the alien's pod, found in Montana the year before.
episodes.title: Wormhole X-treme

episodes.synopsis: At a secret training facility, a young group of cadets are put through their paces by a tough taskmaster: Col. Jack O'Neill.
episodes.title: Proving Ground

episodes.synopsis: An offworld mishap causes an SGC-bound wormhole to prematurely disengage, apparently trapping Teal'c on another planet.
episodes.title: 48 Hours

episodes.synopsis: The Tok'ra have learned of a meeting of the System Lords. Seeing this as an opportunity to cripple the Goa'uld, the Tok'ra enlist the help of SG-1.
episodes.title: Summit

episodes.synopsis: Undercover at the Goa'uld summit, Daniel comes face-to-face with Osiris, who has taken Daniel's ex-girlfriend, Sarah, as his host.
episodes.title: Last Stand

episodes.synopsis: When an asteroid is detected on a collision course with Earth, SG-1 is dispatched to deal with the impending calamity.
episodes.title: Fail Safe

episodes.synopsis: A formidable warrior named K'tano now leads the Jaffa rebellion. He's the former First Prime to the late Goa'uld Imhotep, with hundreds of followers.
episodes.title: The Warrior

episodes.synopsis: A dormant android is discovered on a planet and transported back to Earth for study. At the SGC, it's placed in a secure environment and activated.
episodes.title: Menace

episodes.synopsis: Col. O'Neill must enlist the aid of several convicted felons in a bid to save a planet from the Goa'uld.
episodes.title: The Sentinel

episodes.synopsis: Daniel Jackson returns from an off-world diplomatic mission stricken with radiation poisoning and accused of sabotage by the host government.
episodes.title: Meridian

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 mounts a rescue mission to save Heimdall, an Asgard scientist, and secure an underground laboratory before they fall into the hands of Anubis.
episodes.title: Revelations

episodes.synopsis: Jonas is eager to finish what Dr. Jackson started. The Stargate malfunctions, and Carter informs O'Neill that it could destroy all life on Earth.
episodes.title: Redemption: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The Stargate can only withstand an attack for another 54 hours. Teal'c and his son seek to destroy the weapon that turned the gate into a time bomb.
episodes.title: Redemption: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The team boards a seemingly abandoned Goa'uld ship and is ambushed. The vessel plummets through the atmosphere and crashes into the Pacific Ocean.
episodes.title: Descent

episodes.synopsis: The team investigates a woman found frozen in the ice in the Antarctic. The scientists who discovered her believe she's thousands of years old.
episodes.title: Frozen

episodes.synopsis: Carter, Teal'c and Jonas are dispatched to a small town on the Oregon coast to search for missing research scientist Richard Flemming.
episodes.title: Nightwalkers

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill flees a Jaffa attack but is captured before reaching the Stargate. Imprisoned, O'Neill loses his memory and must rely on a friend to survive.
episodes.title: Abyss

episodes.synopsis: When a delegation from Jonas's home planet claims that a devastating war there is imminent, the Pentagon sends SG-1 to intercede.
episodes.title: Shadow Play

episodes.synopsis: Professors Coombs, Meyers and Felger examine the ruins of a Goa'uld temple. Carter and Jonas are close by, testing equipment near the Stargate.
episodes.title: The Other Guys

episodes.synopsis: The Tok'ra and Jaffa suffer heavy casualties when Anubis's forces overrun SG positions. A scuffle breaks out between Ocker, Tok'ra and Artok.
episodes.title: Allegiance

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team pays a visit to the alien world of Panger, where a working Stargate has recently been discovered among some ruins.
episodes.title: Cure

episodes.synopsis: When television reporter Julia Donovan gets wind of a top-secret project called Prometheus, the president orders Gen. Hammond to kill the story.
episodes.title: Prometheus

episodes.synopsis: After rescuing SG-1 from hyperspace, Asgard leader Thor asks the team to help fight the Replicators that have overrun his home world.
episodes.title: Unnatural Selection

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 team returns from an archeological site on another planet carrying an ancient artifact that glows and emits strange energy waves.
episodes.title: Sight Unseen

episodes.synopsis: When Sen. Kinsey is assassinated in front of witnesses, O'Neill, who was videotaped leaving the scene with a rifle, becomes the prime suspect.
episodes.title: Smoke and Mirrors

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill is at home when Col. Harry Maybourne, the duplicitous agent now wanted for high treason, shows up. O'Neill threatens to turn him in.
episodes.title: Paradise Lost

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 and the Russian SG team travel to a planet to end the heinous experiments Nirrti is conducting on the native population.
episodes.title: Metamorphosis

episodes.synopsis: With Anubis increasing his ability to acquire and use advanced weaponry against Earth, Gen. Hammond decides to break the Stargate program's secrecy.
episodes.title: Disclosure

episodes.synopsis: While on a mission to P2X-005, a planet no human beings are supposed to have visited, O'Neill finds a photograph of a young human woman.
episodes.title: Forsaken

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c is wheeled into surgery. As the surgeon in charge looks at him, the doctor's eyes glow white: He's the Goa'uld System Lord Apophis.
episodes.title: The Changeling

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill is miffed when he's taken off SG missions to baby-sit the commander and crew of the Prometheus on her shakedown cruise.
episodes.title: Memento

episodes.synopsis: The inhabitants of planet P4S-237 believe that the team is the fulfillment of a prophecy that promises them deliverance from their oppressor, Ba'al.
episodes.title: Prophecy

episodes.synopsis: Jackson, who a year before ascended to a higher plane of existence, appears to O'Neill and asks him to prevent Anubis from obtaining the Eye of Ra.
episodes.title: Full Circle

episodes.synopsis: Jonas translates a tablet describing the last city the Ancients were building before the plague. The SG-1 team finds Daniel, but his memory is gone.
episodes.title: Fallen

episodes.synopsis: After capturing Jonas and escaping into hyperspace, Anubis subjects Jonas to a mind probe, then begins an attack on the nation of Kelowna.
episodes.title: Homecoming

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill awakens to find that he's become 30 years younger. When a team of geneticists is put on the case, they discover O'Neill is actually dying.
episodes.title: Fragile Balance

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c is wounded in a fight with the Jaffa. Rya'c and Bra'tac are held captive on Erebus, where Jaffa prisoners are forced to build Ha'tak ships.
episodes.title: Orpheus

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill and the SG-1 team embark on a risky reconnaissance mission to planet P3X-289, which has a highly toxic atmosphere.
episodes.title: Revisions

episodes.synopsis: Soon after the team discovers hundreds of people in cryogenic sleep on a crashed ship, Daniel becomes possessed by the personalities of the sleepers.
episodes.title: Lifeboat

episodes.synopsis: At a mining outpost on P3X-403, an unknown foe captures survey team geologist Lt. Ritter, and Daniel believes the captor is Unas.
episodes.title: Enemy Mine

episodes.synopsis: Carter agrees to help the captain of the Cerberus in winning a perilous race, in exchange for full access to the Serrakins' ion propulsion technology.
episodes.title: Space Race

episodes.synopsis: Felger persuades Hammond to give him another chance, but then creates a computer virus that spreads and shuts down the whole network.
episodes.title: Avenger 2.0

episodes.synopsis: After Jaffa warrior women save the team, they're taken to meet the leader of the rebels, who proposes an alliance between the Hak'tyl and the Tau'ri.
episodes.title: Birthright

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c and Bra'tac are attacked by a black-armored enemy. After he falls, Carter and her father discover that the warrior is a synthetic Goa'uld host.
episodes.title: Evolution: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill heads to Honduras to rescue Daniel. Carter and Teal'c must take out the base where Anubis is using a Goa'uld queen to produce warriors.
episodes.title: Evolution: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: A ship attacks the Prometheus, knocking Carter unconscious. When she awakens, she finds the crew missing, then begins to hallucinate.
episodes.title: Grace

episodes.synopsis: Fearing that the processing of a large vein of Naquadriah may cause the deposit to destroy his homeland, Jonas asks for help to save the planet.
episodes.title: Fallout

episodes.synopsis: Goa'uld lord Osiris visits Daniel in his dreams in the form of Sarah Gardner, his former lover. Carter's relationship with her new beau heats up.
episodes.title: Chimera

episodes.synopsis: Carter and her father are working on a weapon to defeat the army of Anubis drones when Goa'uld ships attack. Carter finds herself pursued by a drone.
episodes.title: Death Knell

episodes.synopsis: A documentary film crew receives a chilly welcome from O'Neill and Hammond. An off-world team finds the remains of a city built by the Ancients.
episodes.title: Heroes: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The film crew continues to document the Stargate program. When a mission goes awry, Stargate Command finds itself under investigation by Sen. Kinsey.
episodes.title: Heroes: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: When the base of a sleeper cell becomes the site of a massacre, the SG-1 team finds evidence of experiments attempting to mix human and Goa'uld DNA.
episodes.title: Resurrection

episodes.synopsis: The joint chiefs of staff brief the president about the Stargate program. But Kinsey has his own plans and tries to get the president to back him.
episodes.title: Inauguration

episodes.synopsis: Stargate Command finds a Repository of the Ancients on planet P3X-439, and O'Neill downloads their knowledge into his brain when Anubis attacks.
episodes.title: Lost City: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: With Anubis ready to attack Earth, O'Neill and Daniel find themselves in a race against the clock to locate the city of the Ancients.
episodes.title: Lost City: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Carter and Teal'c try to contact the Asgard in order to save Jack. Meanwhile, Dr. Weir considers a request for peace talks from the System Lords.
episodes.title: New Order: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Learning the Goa'uld are en route to attack Earth to confirm the existence of an Ancient weapon, Dr. Elizabeth Weir arrests the Goa'uld System Lords.
episodes.title: New Order: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: When Russian Col. Alexi Vaselov visits Stargate Command to request a transfer, he brings with him a contagion that forces SG-1 into lockdown.
episodes.title: Lockdown

episodes.synopsis: As head of Stargate Command, O'Neill has a tough time managing his new duties, which are made worse by an imminent visit from the president.
episodes.title: Zero Hour

episodes.synopsis: Recovering from wounds on a planet that reveres its Stargate as a cultural and religious icon, Jackson tries to prevent a civil war.
episodes.title: Icon

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c goes inside a virtual reality combat training program, but the program won't shut down until either he or it is dead.
episodes.title: Avatar

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c settles in and becomes a protector of his new neighborhood, but not everyone is happy having an alien in the community.
episodes.title: Affinity

episodes.synopsis: Alec Colson, CEO of the global defense contractor Colson Industries, threatens publicly to expose the government's secret war with aliens.
episodes.title: Covenant

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c and his mentor have just returned from Hak'tyl, where they try to convince Ishta to wait until the Jaffa grow numerous enough to wage war.
episodes.title: Sacrifices

episodes.synopsis: When the Stargate vanishes from Stargate Command, Lt. Col. Samantha Carter, Dr. Daniel Jackson and Brig. Gen. Jack O'Neil hunt for the culprits.
episodes.title: Endgame

episodes.synopsis: When the team discovers that Fifth, the Replicator leader, has created a Replicator clone of Lt. Col. Carter, they set out to destroy it.
episodes.title: Gemini

episodes.synopsis: When the Prometheus responds to a distress call apparently sent by a human, they fall into a trap set by a Goa'uld super-soldier.
episodes.title: Prometheus Unbound

episodes.synopsis: O'Neill sends SG-1 to a planet to rescue his treacherous but likable old buddy, Col. Harry Maybourne, from an imminent System Lord attack.
episodes.title: It's Good To Be King

episodes.synopsis: Former vice president Kinsey tells O'Neill that he can help take down the The Trust, a group of rogue NID agents, but their sting goes awry.
episodes.title: Full Alert

episodes.synopsis: A barber from Indiana reveals to O'Neill that he has been having virtual experiences of traveling through the Stargate and being in action with SG-1.
episodes.title: Citizen Joe

episodes.synopsis: Teal'c plans to regain the allegiance of the Jaffa by capturing the Temple of Dakara, which symbolizes the power the Goa'uld have over the Jaffa.
episodes.title: Reckoning: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Hidden in the ruins of the temple on Dakara is an Ancient weapon powerful enough to destroy the Replicators and all life in the galaxy.
episodes.title: Reckoning: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: With the Ancient weapon now in the hands of the Free Jaffa, Anubis plans to reconquer the planet and use the weapon to destroy all life in the galaxy.
episodes.title: Threads

episodes.synopsis: Carter, O'Neill, Daniel and Teal'c travel back to the year 3000 B.C.E. to search for a Zero Point Module in the temple of Ra.
episodes.title: Moebius: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: In an alternate timeline, civilian scientists Carter and Jackson travel to the planet Chulak to help Teal'c repair the altered timeline.
episodes.title: Moebius: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: New commanding officer Gen. Landry and SG-1's new leader, Col. Mitchell, have no time to settle in before the return of the beautiful thief Vala.
episodes.title: Avalon: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Jackson, Teal'c, Mitchell and Vala uncover hidden treasure, including a book that tells the story of the Ancients coming to Earth from another galaxy.
episodes.title: Avalon: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: An Ori priest saves Daniel and Vala from Ori followers. The priest transports them to the Ori holy realm, where Daniel uncovers their secrets.
episodes.title: Origin

episodes.synopsis: After an hour's separation from Daniel, Vala returns to SGC. Mitchell, Jackson and Teal'c must deal with the people Vala has used over the years.
episodes.title: The Ties that Bind

episodes.synopsis: Vala leads SG-1 to the planet where the symbiote that once held her ruled, where the Priors have visited and where the natives worship the Ori.
episodes.title: The Powers that Be

episodes.synopsis: An Ori Prior has established an ever-growing force field on a Jaffa-controlled planet. A minor Goa'uld comes to the SGC to offer his help.
episodes.title: Beachhead

episodes.synopsis: With Vala missing, Mitchell unites SG-1 under his command. A Jaffa warrior turns up dead on a Virginia road, and the team has to figure out why.
episodes.title: Ex Deus Machina

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 investigates a planet that is home to a legendary Jaffa tribe. Mitchell kills one of the Sodan and must battle to the death as punishment.
episodes.title: Babylon

episodes.synopsis: While investigating a black hole, Carter is sent to the wrong planet and discovers a man who is ready to ascend and bring havoc to the Galaxy.
episodes.title: Prototype

episodes.synopsis: A Prior has talked Gerak into following Origin. Teal'c and Bra'tac make a case against the Ori. A plague released by the Ori has breached SGC.
episodes.title: The Fourth Horseman: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The plague continues to spread. Teal'c pleads with the Jaffa High Council to reject Origin. Cameron and Daniel seek the blood of the Prior.
episodes.title: The Fourth Horseman: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: On a planet where the inhabitants can graft memories, Mitchell is arrested for murder. The team believes Mitchell's memory has been implanted.
episodes.title: Collateral Damage

episodes.synopsis: Multiple SG-1 teams arrive through the gate, each one from a parallel universe. Carter, Martouf and Kvasir try to figure out how to close the rift.
episodes.title: Ripple Effect

episodes.synopsis: Two Jaffa council supporters announce they no longer condone the elections. Teal'c and Bra'tac conclude that treachery must be behind their behavior.
episodes.title: Stronghold

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 learns that the Ori have given Rand a superweapon to use against the Caledonian Federation. The team plans to destroy the weapon.
episodes.title: Ethon

episodes.synopsis: During a firefight, SG-1 is forced to fall back to the Stargate, but as Daniel is dialing, both the Stargate and the DHD are mysteriously beamed away.
episodes.title: Off the Grid

episodes.synopsis: The SG-1 members are trapped on a research station where beetles that control an addictive plant prove to be unstoppable carnivores.
episodes.title: The Scourge

episodes.synopsis: Carter and Mitchell enter a parallel dimension. Teal'c and SG-12 travel to a planet where a village is exterminated by its own hero, Volnek.
episodes.title: Arthur's Mantle

episodes.synopsis: The Ori send Vala through a black hole to their home galaxy, where she learns that they plan to invade the Milky Way through a supergate.
episodes.title: Crusade

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 travels to Camelot to find a device that can help them defeat the Ori. They investigate a library guarded by a hologram called the Black Knight.
episodes.title: Camelot

episodes.synopsis: Following their defeat by the Ori motherships, the team struggles to reunite in the face of this seemingly unbeatable foe.
episodes.title: Flesh and Blood

episodes.synopsis: On a mission to find a weapon that will defeat the Ori, the team discovers a planet whose inhabitants were killed by a mysterious illness.
episodes.title: Morpheus

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 journeys to Atlantis with a new plan to defend the galaxy from Ori.
episodes.title: The Pegasus Project

episodes.synopsis: When the team makes a pact with an old enemy to fight their common foe, the results are disastrous.
episodes.title: Insiders

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 struggles to control a rash of brutal attacks by an elusive and savage alien creature.
episodes.title: Uninvited

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 attempts to assist Martin Lloyd (Willie Garson) with his feature film script as a cover story to keep the Stargate Program secret.
When the Jaffa modify an ancient device so that it is capable of defeating the Ori, Adria (Morena Baccarin) leads an attack on Dakara.
episodes.title: Counterstrike

episodes.synopsis: When Vala is kidnapped by trust members acting under the orders of the Goa'uld Athena, an accident causes her to lose all memory of who she is.
episodes.title: Memento Mori

episodes.synopsis: Mitchell goes undercover to track down the Odyssey, which was attacked and boarded by members of the Lucian Alliance.
episodes.title: Company of Thieves

episodes.synopsis: SG-1 finds the planet where they believe the Sangraal is located, and undertake a quest to find it.
episodes.title: The Quest: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Discovering the frozen body of Merlin, SG-1 works to help him build the Sangraal before Adria and her Ori army can track them down.
episodes.title: The Quest: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: While hoping to use Merlin's phasing device to hide a village, Mitchell and an injured Carter hide themselves from an occupation of Ori soldiers.
episodes.title: Line in the Sand

episodes.synopsis: An experiment goes wrong, leaving Carter trapped in a parallel reality where martial law has been enforced and the Earth is under attack from the Ori.
episodes.title: The Road Not Taken

episodes.synopsis: When Jackson turns up as a Prior asking SG-1 to aid him in a plan, it's up to the team to not only save Jackson's life but possibly end the war.
episodes.title: The Shroud

episodes.synopsis: After Netan (Eric Steinberg) and the Lucian Alliance are undermined by SG-1, he yet again decides to put a bounty on their heads.
episodes.title: Bounty

episodes.synopsis: Mistaken for rebels on an alien planet, SG-1 must become hostage takers in order to buy themselves enough time to be rescued before they're executed.
episodes.title: Bad Guys

episodes.synopsis: Barely surviving the bombing massacre of a Jaffa summit, Teal'c must track down and stop a Jaffa leader who plans to take control of the Jaffa nation.
episodes.title: Talion

episodes.synopsis: Vala's father, Jacek, contacts Stargate Command, wishing to offer information about a series of planned attacks on Earth in exchange for sanctuary.
episodes.title: Family Ties

episodes.synopsis: In an elaborate plan using Vala as bait to capture Adria, SG-1's crew members are surprised when Ba'al intercepts Adria to use in his own evil plan.
episodes.title: Dominion

episodes.synopsis: With the extinction imminent, the Asgard give all their knowledge and technology to SG-1, but not before the Ori launch an attack trying to intercede.
episodes.title: Unending
